plough /plaʊ/

(ploughing,ploughed,ploughs) [英国英语] AM  plow 

1. N-COUNT A plough is a large farming tool with sharp blades that is pulled across the soil to turn it over, usually before seeds are planted. 犁 

例： There are new tractors and new ploughs in the machinery lot. 机器设备场里有新拖拉机和新耕犁。 

2.  →  see also snowplough 

3. V-T When someone ploughs an area of land, they turn over the soil using a plough. 犁 (地) 

例： They were no longer using mules and horses to plough their fields. 他们那时已不再用骡子和马来犁地了。

